Autolatina, Volkswagen AG&lt;VOWG.F> and Ford Motor Co's &lt;F> Latin American joint venture,was expected to make losses of 500 mln marks from Brazilianoperations in 1987, VW spokesman Ortwin Witzel said.    He could not comment on a report in the FrankfurterRundschau daily that Ford might pull out of the venture, set upin 1986 to incorporate VW's and Ford's Brazilian and Argentineoperations. Ford holds 49 pct of Autolatina.    Witzel blamed Autolatina's losses on Brazil's governmentprice restrictions but said the losses were in line withexpectations. VW's Brazil unit lost 258 mln marks in 1986. Reuter&#3;